Sentencas: Nd2NiO4+delta (NNO)-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 (delta) (CGO) composites were investigated as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Fabrication and electrochemical characterizations of Nd2NiO4+δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ composite cathodes for anode-supported intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Planar NiO-YSZ anode-supported cells in size of 50 mm x 50 mm were fabricated with YSZ as the electrolyte.
Titulo: Fabrication and electrochemical characterizations of Nd2NiO4+δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ composite cathodes for anode-supported intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of sintering temperature and the relative proportions of NNO and CGO on the cell performance were investigated in combination with chemical reactivity tests of NNO-YSZ and NNO-CGO.
Titulo: Fabrication and electrochemical characterizations of Nd2NiO4+δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ composite cathodes for anode-supported intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: NNO-CGO composite cathodes were successfully sintered on YSZ electrolyte at 1000 degrees C. By using La0.6Sr0.4CoO3 (delta) (LSC) as current collector, the cell with 70NNO-30CGO composite cathode sintered at 1000 degrees C exhibited the highest power density of 620 mW cm (2) (at 0.7 V) and the lowest polarization resistance of 0.302 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C. Short-term durability studies revealed that the degradation of cell performance was attributed to the crack formation on the LSC current collector layer and the delamination between NNO-CGO cathode layer and LSC current collector layer.
Titulo: Fabrication and electrochemical characterizations of Nd2NiO4+δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-δ composite cathodes for anode-supported intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
